`∑ j in s \ {i}, (c j / (∑ k in s, c k)) • x j = ∑ j in s \ {i}, w' j • x j`

This implies:
`∑ j in s \ {i}, ((c j / (∑ k in s, c k)) - w' j) • x j = 0`

This is true if `c j / (∑ k in s, c k) = w' j` for all `j ∈ s \ {i}`.

But we don't know this. The weights `w'` are part of the hypothesis `hy i hi`.

So the proof is incorrect. We need to find another way.

The correct approach is to use the hypothesis `hy i hi` directly. It states that `y i ∈ convexHull 𝕜 (x '' (s \ {i}))`. This means there exists a function `w' : (s \ {i}) → 𝕜` such that:
1. `∀ j ∈ s \ {i}, 0 ≤ w' j`
2. `∑ j in s \ {i}, w' j = 1`
3. `y i = ∑ j in s \ {i}, w' j • x j`

So we can construct the required weights as:
```tactics
      refine ⟨fun j hj => w' j / (∑ k in s \ {i}, w' k), by
        intro j hj
        have hwj : 0 ≤ w' j := hw' j hj
        have hsum_nonneg : 0 ≤ ∑ k in s \ {i}, w' k := by
          apply Finset.sum_nonneg
          intro k hk
          apply hw' k hk
        have hsum_pos : 0 < ∑ k in s \ {i}, w' k := by
          have h_nonempty : (s \ {i}).Nonempty := by
            use i
            simp [hs.mem_sdiff, hs.mem_singleton]
            tauto
          have h_card_pos : 0 < (s \ {i}).card := by
            exact h_nonempty.card_pos
          have h_sum_pos : 0 < ∑ k in s \ {i}, w' k := by
            apply Finset.sum_pos
            · intro k hk
              apply hw' k hk
            · use i
              simp [hs.mem_sdiff, hs.mem_singleton]
              tauto
          exact h_sum_pos
        apply div_nonneg
        · exact hwj
        · exact hsum_nonneg
      ⟩
```

We also need to prove `∑ w i = 1`.
```tactics
      have hsum_eq_one : ∑ i in s, (w' i / (∑ k in s \ {i}, w' k)) = 1 := by
        have hsum_nonneg : 0 ≤ ∑ k in s \ {i}, w' k := by
          apply Finset.sum_nonneg
          intro k hk
          apply hw' k hk
        have hsum_pos : 0 < ∑ k in s \ {i}, w' k := by
          have h_nonempty : (s \ {i}).Nonempty := by
            use i
            simp [hs.mem_sdiff, hs.mem_singleton]
            tauto
          have h_card_pos : 0 < (s \ {i}).card := by
            exact h_nonempty.card_pos
          have h_sum_pos : 0 < ∑ k in s \ {i}, w' k := by
            apply Finset.sum_pos
            · intro k hk
              apply hw' k hk
            · use i
              simp [hs.mem_sdiff, hs.mem_singleton]
              tauto
          exact h_sum_pos
        field_simp [hsum_pos]
        <;> ring
```

Finally, we need to prove that for all `i ∈ s`, `(s \ {i}).centerMass w x = y i`.
```tactics
      refine ⟨hsum_eq_one, ?_⟩
      intro i hi
      have h1 : y i ∈ affineSpan 𝕜 (x '' (s \ {i})) := by
        simpa using hy i hi
      simp [Finset.mem_sdiff, Finset.mem_singleton] at h1 ⊢
      rcases h1 with ⟨w', hw', hw_eq'⟩
      have h2 : (s \ {i}).centerMass (fun j hj => w' j / (∑ k in s \ {i}, w' k)) x = y i := by
        simp [centerMass, hw_eq']
        <;> field_simp [show 0 < ∑ k in s \ {i}, w' k by
          have h_nonempty : (s \ {i}).Nonempty := by
            use i
            simp [hs.mem_sdiff, hs.mem_singleton]
            tauto
          have h_card_pos : 0 < (s \ {i}).card := by
            exact h_nonempty.card_pos
          have h_sum_pos : 0 < ∑ k in s \ {i}, w' k := by
            apply Finset.sum_pos
            · intro k hk
              apply hw' k hk
            · use i
              simp [hs.mem_sdiff, hs.mem_singleton]
              tauto
          exact h_sum_pos
        ]
        <;> ring
      simpa using h2
